{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c377d1de-801d-4ff0-aa71-90ea01f9ced8","content":"No repo-specific content here, so this is general guidance:\n\n## Migrating from `VSTest@3` to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n### 1. Update your test projects\n\nIn each `.csproj`, enable the new runner:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nUpgrade `MSTest` to **v3.x+** (ships with the platform).\n\n### 2. Replace `VSTest@3` in your pipeline\n\nThe new runner produces **standalone executables** — use `dotnet test` (or run the EXEs directly) instead of the VSTest task:\n\n```yaml\n# Before\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**\\*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)\\TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n\n# After\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run Tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish Test Results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish Code Coverage'\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### 3. Key differences\n\n| Concern | VSTest@3 | New approach |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | vstest.console | In-process (exe) |\n| TRX reports | Built-in | `--logger trx` |\n| Code coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` |\n| Publish results | Automatic | Explicit `PublishTestResults@2` |\n\n### 4. Tips\n- Add `condition: always()` to publish tasks so results are reported even on test failure.\n- For Cobertura output (needed by `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2`), add the `Microsoft.CodeCoverage` NuGet or use `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=Cobertura\"`.\n- Run `dotnet test` with `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` to catch hung tests in CI.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d6a585d6-bee8-43df-9bdf-d4e94cad98c1","outputTokens":649,"requestId":"0436:1CF5FA:1DE76EE:21BAFF5:69E81A6A"},"id":"af9ec5ef-1a70-42ef-802a-3306bb65d6b4","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:46:47.193Z","parentId":"09854b3c-f40f-4fec-8e29-ee903cff1b2e"}
